Description: Fragment of disc foot and floor of East Greek pottery cup; flat foot with small central hole; remains of painted rosette or the like on floor; edge of foot and adjacent parts of top and underside irregularly glazed, rest reserved; graffito under.
Bibliographic references: Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 229)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.220)
